     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d256n1-ptr" id="PJA05d256n1">1</a>
      <p>Not found.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d256n2-ptr" id="PJA05d256n2">2</a>
      <p>In a daring raid Col. William Barton of Rhode Island in the summer of 1777 captured Maj. Gen. Richard Prescott and his aide, for which feat the congress had awarded Barton an elegant sword. The congress also gave formal recognition to Lt. Col. Marinus Willett, Col. Peter Gansevoort, and Brig. Gen. Nicholas Herkimer for their bravery in repelling St. Legers forces (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 8:580, 709; 9:771772). Smith remains unidentified.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d256n3-ptr" id="PJA05d256n3">3</a>
      <p>Word supplied from Letterbook.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d256n4-ptr" id="PJA05d256n4">4</a>
      <p>Rev. Jacob Duch, whose prayers had inspired early sessions of the congress, became a loyalist in 1777 (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Allen Johnson and Dumas Malone, eds., &lt;i&gt;Dictionary of American Biography&lt;/i&gt;, New York, 19281936; 20 vols. plus index and supplements. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">DAB</span></span>).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d256n5-ptr" id="PJA05d256n5">5</a>
      <p>Rush resigned on 30 Jan. (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington C. Ford and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 17741789&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 19041937; 34 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 10:101).</p>
     </div>
